msgid "Workshop Administration workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:3
msgid "For centrally organized workshops"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:5
msgid "One of the following occurs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:6
msgid "Someone submits the Carpentries workshop request form"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:7
msgid "Someone emails team@carpentries.org to request a workshop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:8
msgid "Someone contacts a staff member to request a workshop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:10
msgid ""
"Workshop & Logistics Manager or the Regional Coordinators for that region"
" responds to request by email or phone/video call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:11
msgid "Give them more information about the Carpentries as needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:12
msgid "Software Carpentry lessons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:13
msgid "Data Carpentry lessons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:14
msgid "Library Carpentry lessons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:15
msgid "Ask them for more information about their request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:16
msgid "Who is their target population?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:17
msgid "What curriculum content do they want to cover?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:18
msgid "What timeframe are they looking to host a workshop?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:19
msgid "Remind them we need 2-3 months notice"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:20
msgid ""
"Remind them to consider their own schedule and other events that may "
"affect things like room availability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:21
msgid "Remind them of the budget"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:22
msgid ""
"US$2500 standard fee due to our fiscal sponsor (for non-member "
"university, government, or non-profit sites only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:23
msgid ""
"Costs for instructor travel (airfare, ground travel, hotel, and "
"meals/incidentals) are managed entirely between host and instructors. We "
"will look for local instructors but can not guarantee it. Member sites "
"are still responsible for travel costs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:24
msgid "Ask them to complete the official request form"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:25
msgid ""
"Workshop & Logistics Manager or the Regional Coordinators records request"
" form in AMY."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:27
msgid ""
"For non-member sites, Regional Coordinator asks host for invoicing "
"contact, and introduces them to the Administrative Support Specialist to "
"begin the invoicing process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:29
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator adds workshop to appropriate tab (by geography) on "
"call for instructors sign up sheet and sends email to instructors list "
"notifying them of upcoming opportunities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:31
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator reviews list of instructors signed up as interested "
"in upcoming workshops and tentatively places them based on experience, "
"geography, and skill set. See blog post for details.  Selection "
"guidelines include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:33
msgid ""
"Other workshops has that person signed up for in that time period  If "
"they have volunteered to teach three workshops over the next few months, "
"we likely wonâ€™t place them at all of them. However, we will take "
"advantage of their flexibility to get them in on at least one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:34
msgid ""
"Each person's experience with The Carpentries We want to be sure to match"
" up experienced instructors with new instructors, so new instructors are "
"supported by experienced instructors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:35
msgid ""
"Each person's skill set with Carpentries material  We want to make sure "
"each instructor is comfortable teaching the workshop content, and "
"understands the other instructor's skills."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:36
msgid ""
"Each person's acadmic or professional domain It can be helpful, but not "
"required, to match the instructors' domain with the workshop audience. "
"Instructors get opportunities to network in their fields, and learners "
"get to hear from people working in those same fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:37
msgid ""
"Geography While we do not guarantee local instructors at workshops, we do"
" take this in consideration to keep the host site's cost down and to help"
" build local communities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:39
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator emails these instructors to confirm their "
"availability, and returns back to the other instructors on the list if a "
"conflict has since come up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:41
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator sends email to workshop instructors and hosts with "
"introductory information.  This includes links to guides for roles of "
"host, instructor, and helper."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:43
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator emails everyone else who signed up for that event "
"thanking them for their time, letting them know other instructors were "
"placed, and encouraging them to sign up for other opportunities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:45
#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:65
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator reminds instructors to set up a workshop website "
"using the workshop template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:48
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator sets up surveys in Survey Monkey and emails results "
"links to hosts and instructors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:50
msgid "If needed Regional Coordinator sets up registration in Eventbrite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:51
msgid ""
"If there is a registration fee,Regional Coordinator informs Business "
"Administrator that this will need to be refunded or applied to the "
"workshop invoice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:53
msgid ""
"In weeks leading up to workshop, Regional Coordinator sends check in "
"emails to be sure planning is progressing smoothly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:55
#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:74
msgid ""
"After workshop is over Regional Coordinator sends email asking how things"
" went and collecting attendance data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:57
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator records workshop attendance in AMY, and if "
"additional information is provided, in the Workshop Documents GitHub "
"repo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:59
msgid "For self organized workshops"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:61
msgid ""
"Instructors notify Regional Coordinator about upcoming self organized "
"workshop. This is no fee (suggested or mandated) for a self organized "
"workshop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:63
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator reminds them that as a self organized workshop they "
"will have access to our surveys but will not receive any other support in"
" coordinating this workshop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:68
msgid "Regional Coordinator records this in AMY."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:70
msgid ""
"Regional Coordinator sets up surveys in Survey Monkey and emails results "
"links to hosts and instructors. Explain to the hosts and instructors that"
" this link should not be shared. Regional Coordinator informs hosts and "
"instructors where to find the pre and post survey links to distribute to "
"learners."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:72
msgid ""
"In weeks leading up to workshop, Regional Coordinator sends check in "
"emails to be sure planning is progressing smoothly. This is optional as "
"instructors and hosts should not be expecting direct support from us."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/workshop_administration/workshop_admin_workflow.md:76
msgid "Regional Coordinator records workshop attendance in AMY."
msgstr ""

